(438, 435, 1, 'install-repair-tool', 'Install/repair tool for Skeleton', 14, 1, 1, 1, 1, 'Details on what the installer/repairer should do.', 'Authentication Installer should check authentication at the very start and then re affirm authentication on every page load using a session hash If config inc php does not exist It should check that a valid MySQL username password and hostname was supplied If config inc php does exist It should try to check that a valid root node administrator has logged in On a successful login it should issue a session hash This hash should depend on the user and IP and time and a secret code made of the username and password of the logged in user or the username and password for the database Bootstrapping By this time we should either have a valid connection to a database server but not necessarily knowing which database and prefix to use or a valid connection chosen database and logged in user If the database and prefix aren t known yet give the user some options Go hunting around all visible databases for existing Skeleton installations List these to the user and allow the user to repair this existing installation Go hunting around for all visible databases which we have CREATE permission in List these to the user and allow the user to start a new installation in these databases Check if we have CREATE DATABASE and GRANT permissions in the database server If so list this an option under start a new installation The default value should be repair this existing installation if there are existing ones found The pre selected installation can be the one with the node table having the latest creation date If there are no existing installations found the default and only option will be start a new installation The pre selected value should be to create a new database if possible otherwise it should be the existing writable database with the fewest tables Checking for existing installations should consist of Check for table names ending in node path and user Each installation must have all three of them with the same prefix The node table must have columns named node_ID node_parentID and node_title Setting up tables Now tables should be set up as done in definetables inc php Check writeable directories These directories should all be writeable If they aren t halt with an error message explaining that they need to be made writeable Otherwise move right along no need to display anything Cache directory Data directory Templates directory and directory for each style and any c directories below those Initialise database Initialise database Create node sets Always create set of admin nodes Optionally create other node sets based on checkboxes ticked by user Examples may include Privacy policy About us page Blog Sample article categories Node sets should have the ability to search for existing page matches based on a wide range of criteria including types of children proximity to root node and more They should have the ability to set custom permissions including those for known admin or editor groups Check database consistency Use existing consistencycheck Note checking nodes and paths not yet complete will have to implement a way to move recovered nodes to an inactive folder Clean up Rebuild permission tables Rebuild node relationships table Re compile templates Wipe data cache Write config inc php Based on template in includes system configtemplate tpl php If file isn t writeable display on screen in a textarea or similar for copying and pasting', 'should,database,node,existing,user,installation,check,create,php,directory', 1206760373, 1208086872, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(441, 435, 1, 'initialise-database-procedure', 'Initialise database procedure', 14, 1, 1, 1, 1, '', 'Group user groupuser permission and add permission Give the everybody group view access to the root node unless there were already any permissions in the permissions table Either the user logs in as a root node admin or the user didn t log in and config inc php doesn t exist If the user didn t log in ask them to supply username password and email address for themselves and create a user based on this Check that the user has full access to the root node of the application and at least view and admin access everywhere else If so continue If not Check if the user is in an admin usergroup already to which no other person belongs If not create a new admin group specifically for them Grant full access to the root node for the user s admin group and eliminate any other permission which would deny them admin or view access anywhere else If there isn t one with the name already create a group called editors and give them all permissions except admin permission throughout the site At root node grant admin group and editors group if it seems to have the default set of perms appropriate creation permissions for each type Types should have the ability to suggest add permissions for administrators and editors Iterate through the installed types and give add permissions for the admin group and editors group if it was the default or new at root node Action type and trinket The installed modules should give values for their entry in the action items or trinkets table If there is an existing value for an icon and it seems to point to a valid file then leave it otherwise always overwrite with official values from module Node and path Make sure there is a root node If there isn t create one with an appropriate type Make sure that there is a path for the root node and it is valid If not create a path Try to base its URL on the currently used URL Ask the user if necessary Useroption Inser